description: Protect upstream CircuitPython and MicroPython clones in cmods from git commits
alwaysApply: true
---

# cmods upstream repos — do not commit

The `~/github/cmods` workspace contains git repos. Two of them are **upstream clones, not owned repos**:

- `~/github/cmods/circuitpython/`
- `~/github/cmods/micropython/`

**Never** stage, commit, push, or open PRs for changes inside those directories unless the user explicitly overrides this rule for a specific action.

Local patches there (LVGL integration, board configs, generated parser tables, etc.) are expected to remain uncommitted working-tree changes.

All other repos under `~/github/cmods` (including the `cmods` root repo) may be committed and pushed when the user asks.

To sync owned repos on demand, use the `/push-cmods` slash command.
